Started in 2015 for my welfare. Added and updated some notes in 2018.


1. Download CE versionof Docker.
   https://store.docker.com/editions/community/docker-ce-server-ubuntu
   Login to your account. You really don't have to.
2.
   sudo apt-get install \
   linux-image-extra-$(uname -r) \
   linux-image-extra-virtual
3. apt-get install \
   apt-transport-https \
   ca-certificates \
   curl \
   software-properties-common
4.
 curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo apt-key add -
5. verify: apt-key fingerprint 0EBFCD88
6. Becuase I use Linux Mint since base Ubuntu sucks: I had to type the version
in manually: https://linuxmint.com/download_all.php
add-apt-repository \
   "deb [arch=amd64] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
   xenial \
   stable"

7a. sudo apt-get update 
7b. sudo apt-get install docker-ce

8. Setup the initial docker
   docker run hello-world

Some notes: """

To try something more ambitious, you can run an Ubuntu container with:
 $ docker run -it ubuntu bash

Share images, automate workflows, and more with a free Docker ID:
 https://cloud.docker.com/

